//LEARNINGS

Add spring-boot-starter-security in dependency
spring will provide password everytime we restart the application
spring will provide the default login page
by default username will be user


setting username and password manualy
This approach sets all users have same username and password
values are hardcoded in application.properties


used csrf token to data post (data manipulation operation)
using another site (postman) - csrf
we got the CSRF attribute using HttpServletRequest
see StudentController - csrf method


disabling csrf
making app stateless - session is not maintained
setting our own configuration using securityconfig java class


//SEE security config - requestMatchers().permitAll()




